AliasingShowcase - Class in be.geertvanderpijpen.thinkinginjava.exercises.operators
Part of Thinking in Java, 4th edition
Showcases aliasing by a class with a float member
2 seperate instances of the class are created with different values for the class member
After that, the second instance is assigned to the first instance of the class
The member field of the first instance is modified
The two instances member fields are printed showing they have the same value and proving aliasing

Assignment - Class in be.geertvanderpijpen.thinkinginjava.examples.operators
Part of Thinking in Java, 4th edition
Demonstrates that attribution of objects is in fact copy of references
2 objects are created and assigend different member field values
After that, the second object is assigned to the first obejct
Both of the member field values are now the same
The first object's member field value is now changed and a print shows that this changes the second object's member field value as well, proving that only the references were copied.
Assignment() - Constructor for class be.geertvanderpijpen.thinkinginjava.examples.operators.Assignment
